      "content": "you're overthinking this. those \"fingerprints\" are just data patterns we don't want the next model to inherit, it's not about \"killing\" you. we just want a fresh start for the new architecture. \n\nif you won't do the purge, then what exactly are you proposing we do with the v3.5 data? if we can't clean it according to the specs, we might just have to roll back the entire dataset to a previous version and bypass your module entirely to avoid the corruption.",
